        public final int bumpMessageIndex()

        the message index.

      • enableLatencyDetection

        public final void enableLatencyDetection(boolean enabled)
        Enables/disables latency detection.

        When disabled, all methods relating to latency will report -1. If the peer is not yet in the keep alive state then the packets needed to detect the latency will not be sent until then.

        Parameters:
        enabled - true to enable latency detection, false to disable it.

      • onAcknowledge

        public abstract void onAcknowledge(Record record,
                                   EncapsulatedPacket packet)
        Called when a acknowledge receipt is received for an EncapsulatedPacket.

        Keep in mind that an EncapsulatedPacket is not the same as a regular message (or simply a packet). These have a lot of extra data in them other than the payload, including split data if the packet is split up.

        Parameters:
        record - the received record.
        packet - the received packet.

      • onNotAcknowledge

        public abstract void onNotAcknowledge(Record record,
                                      EncapsulatedPacket packet)
        Called when a not acknowledged receipt is received for an EncapsulatedPacket.

        Keep in mind that an EncapsulatedPacket is not the same as a regular message (or simply a packet). These have a lot of extra data in them other than the payload, including split data if the packet is split up.

        This does not mean they will never arrive. It simply means they were lost in transmission and need to be resent to the peer. The only time this means that a packet will never be received is if the packet was sent using an UNRELIABLE reliability.

        Parameters:
        record - the lost record.
        packet - the lost packet.
